<h2 id="cheatsheets-and-reference-guides">Cheatsheets and Reference Guides</h2>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://www.rstudio.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/data-wrangling-cheatsheet.pdf">dyplyr cheat sheet</a> (data wrangling)</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.rstudio.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/ggplot2-cheatsheet.pdf">ggplot cheat sheet</a> (data visualization)</li>
  <li><a href="https://rstudio.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/rmarkdown-cheatsheet.pdf">R Markdown Cheatsheet</a> (reproducibility and communication of results)</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.rstudio.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/base-r.pdf">Base R cheat sheet</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://cran.r-project.org/doc/contrib/Short-refcard.pdf">R Reference Card</a></li>
</ul>

<h2 id="troubleshooting">Troubleshooting</h2>

<ul>
  <li><a href="http://rseek.org">rseek</a> (search most online R documentation and discussion forums)</li>
  <li><a href="http://www.burns-stat.com/documents/books/the-r-inferno">R inferno</a> (useful for troubleshooting)</li>
</ul>

